/**
 * AutoBiddingEngine - Core service for automatic bidding orchestration
 *
 * ## Purpose
 * Manages the automatic bidding workflow when new manual bids are placed on an auction.
 * Coordinates proxy bid evaluation, auto-bid placement, and logging.
 *
 * @package    WooCommerce Auction
 * @subpackage Services
 * @version    1.0.0
 * @requirement REQ-AB-001: Automatic bidding engine
 * @requirement REQ-AB-002: Place auto-bids when manual bids placed
 * @requirement REQ-AB-004: Performance requirements (< 1s for 100 proxies)
 * @requirement REQ-AB-005: Audit logging for all attempts
 *
 * ## UML Class Diagram
 *
 * ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
 * │         AutoBiddingEngine                       │
 * ├─────────────────────────────────────────────────┤
 * │ - enabled: bool                                 │
 * │ - proxy_repository: ProxyBidRepository          │
 * │ - log_repository: AutoBidLogRepository          │
 * │ - proxy_service: ProxyBidService                │
 * │ - calculator: BidIncrementCalculator            │
 * ├─────────────────────────────────────────────────┤
 * │ + handleNewBid(): void                          │
 * │ + setEnabled(bool): self                        │
 * │ + setCalculator(): self                         │
 * │ + getAuctionStatistics(): array                 │
 * └─────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
 *            ▲
 *            │ uses
 *            ├─────────────────────┬────────────────┬─────────────────┐
 *            │                     │                │                 │
 *  ┌──────────────────────┐ ┌──────────────────┐ ┌──────────────────┐ ┌──────────────┐
 *  │ ProxyBidRepository   │ │ ProxyBidService  │ │ BidIncrement    │ │ AutoBidLog  │
 *  │                      │ │                  │ │ Calculator      │ │ Repository  │
 *  │ + findActive...()    │ │ + updateCurrent..│ │ + calculate()   │ │ + log()     │
 *  │ + findById()         │ │ + markOutbid()   │ │                 │ │ + getStats()│
 *  └──────────────────────┘ └──────────────────┘ └──────────────────┘ └──────────────┘
 *
 * ## Interaction Flow (Message Sequence Diagram)
 *
 *  Manual Bid Placed
 *        │
 *        ▼
 *   handleNewBid()
 *        │
 *        ├─ Find active proxies for auction
 *        │       │
 *        │       ▼
 *        │   [For each proxy]
 *        │       │
 *        │       ├─ Skip if same user as bidder
 *        │       │
 *        │       ├─ Check if proxy max >= required bid
 *        │       │       │
 *        │       │       ├─ YES → Place auto-bid via ProxyBidService
 *        │       │       │              │
 *        │       │       │              └─ updateCurrentBid()
 *        │       │       │
 *        │       │       └─ NO → Mark as outbid via ProxyBidService
 *        │       │              │
 *        │       │              └─ markOutbid()
 *        │
 *        └─ Log all attempts to AutoBidLogRepository
 *
 * ## Strategies
 * 1. Enabled/Disabled: Engine can be disabled for testing or maintenance
 * 2. Calculator Injectable: Supports different bid increment strategies
 * 3. Fail-Safe: Exceptions logged, don't crash workflow
 * 4. Performance Optimized: Batch operations, minimize DB calls
 *
 * ## Dependencies
 * - ProxyBidRepository: Access active proxy bids
 * - AutoBidLogRepository: Record all attempts
 * - ProxyBidService: Update proxy bid status
 * - BidIncrementCalculator: Calculate next bid amounts
 *
 * ## Example Usage
 *
 * ```php
 * $engine = new AutoBiddingEngine(
 *     $proxy_repo,
 *     $log_repo,
 *     $proxy_service,
 *     $calculator
 * );
 *
 * // Enable auto-bidding
 * $engine->setEnabled(true);
 *
 * // Use percentage increment strategy
 * $engine->setCalculator(
 *     new BidIncrementCalculator(
 *         BidIncrementCalculator::STRATEGY_PERCENTAGE,
 *         ['percentage' => 0.10]
 *     )
 * );
 *
 * // Process when new bid placed
 * $engine->handleNewBid(
 *     $auction_id = 100,
 *     $new_bid_amount = 150.00,
 *     $bidder_user_id = 50,
 *     $previous_bidder_id = 1
 * );
 *
 * // Get statistics
 * $stats = $engine->getAuctionStatistics(100);
 * echo $stats['total_attempts']; // 5
 * echo $stats['successful_attempts']; // 3
 * ```
 *
 * ## Performance Considerations
 * - REQ-AB-004: Must process 100 proxy bids in under 1 second
 * - Uses indexed queries on auction_id and status
 * - Batch operations to minimize database round-trips
 * - Lazy loading of bid increment calculator configuration
 *
 * ## Logging Strategy (REQ-AB-005)
 * Every call to handleNewBid() generates log entries:
 * - 1 entry per proxy bid evaluated (success or failure)
 * - Includes processing time, bid amount, user IDs
 * - Status codes: PLACED, OUTBID, SKIPPED
 *
 * ## Error Handling
 * - Exceptions from ProxyBidService caught and logged
 * - Invalid state transitions logged as warnings
 * - Business logic errors caught separately from system errors
 *
 * @see ProxyBidService for proxy bid status updates
 * @see BidIncrementCalculator for bid increment strategies
 * @see AutoBidLogRepository for audit trail storage
 * @see ProxyBid for proxy bid entity reference
 */
class AutoBiddingEngine {
    // ... implementation details ...
}
